                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kw5814t/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the eighth day. It has afflicted every one of<lb/> us. We hang down\n                                        our heads with shame.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I was lately in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>,\n                                        and was<lb/> warmly welcomed. Whilst there, somebody\n                                        told<lb/> me that the <placeName>N. O.</placeName>\n                                        congregation had written me an<lb/> invitation to come and\n                                        be their minister, but if so,<lb/> the letter has never\n                                        reached my hands. <persName>Carillon</persName><lb/> applied\n                                        to me to give him letters of introduction<lb/> and\n                                        recommendation in order to obtain the<lb/> situation. I\n                                        declined doing so, and gave him<lb/> as my reasons, his\n                                        uniform bad conduct in <add>?</add><lb/> dissension and\n                                        propagating improper and heterodox<lb/> doctrine. His\n                                        eloquence did not move me. I<lb/> also refused to preach for\n                                        him in <placeName>Spanish Town</placeName>, as<lb/> I would\n                                        not aid him in the principle of sending<lb/> round the\n                                        begging box for his benefit.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Pray give my best respects to <persName>Miss<lb/>\n                                                  Gratz</persName> and all her family; to my friends\n                                                  <persName>Mrs Hart</persName><lb/> and\n                                                  <persName>Miss Louisa</persName>, <persName>Mr\n                                                  Abr. Hart</persName> &amp; family, <persName>Mr\n                                                  Peixotto</persName><lb/> your good land lady and\n                                                  <persName>Miss Couzens</persName>, if she be\n                                                  <persName>miss<lb/> Couzens</persName> still, and\n                                        all my kind well wishers, send<lb/> me 100 of the Roads of\n                                        faith. I hope you corrected<lb/> any errors without regard\n                                        to my vanity or self-<lb/>love. Wishing you success in all\n                                        your undertakings<lb/> in which <persName>Mrs\n                                                  Nathan</persName> and family <add>?</add>.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">I am</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">as ever</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">Truly &amp; sincerely yours</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">M N Nathan</persName>\n                              </p>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kw5814t/canvas/p4"
                }
